ns%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-fighter-jet-fleet-growing-size-capability-pentagon-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eoriginal%20J-10%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20in%202022.%20They%20can%20carry%20bombs%2C%20air-to-air%20missiles%2C%20and%20rockets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERelentlessly%20upgraded%20since%20its%20debut%20in%20the%202000s%2C%20the%20J-10%20is%20Beijing's%20answer%20to%20Western%20light%20fighters%20such%20as%20the%20American%20F-16%20and%20Sweden's%20Saab%20Gripen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese-designed%20and%20manufactured%20jet%20could%20prove%20to%20be%20a%20game%20changer%20on%20the%20global%20arms%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Jordan%2C%20a%20senior%20lecturer%20in%20defence%20studies%20at%20King's%20College%20London%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%3A%20%26quot%3BThink%20of%20the%20J-10C%20as%20roughly%20equivalent%20to%20a%20late-model%20F-16%2C%20but%20with%20some%20features%20%E2%80%94%20like%20its%20long-range%20missile%20suite%20%E2%80%94%20that%20could%20give%20it%20the%20edge%20in%20certain%20scenarios.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20J-10%20was%20China's%20first%20major%20attempt%20to%20produce%20a%20modern%2C%20homegrown%20combat%20aircraft.%20It%20entered%20service%20in%202004%20as%20the%20J-10A%2C%20a%20single-engine%2C%20multirole%20fighter%20with%20a%20canard-delta%20wing%20configuration%20%E2%80%94%20a%20design%20choice%20that%20prioritizes%20agility%20over%20stability%2C%20giving%20it%20manoeuvrability%20in%20dogfights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20J-10%20was%20designed%20to%20be%20flexible%20and%20equally%20capable%20in%20air-to-air%20combat%20and%20ground-attack%20missions.%20It%20can%20carry%20a%20mix%20of%20precision-guided%20bombs%2C%20anti-ship%20missiles%2C%20and%20medium-range%20air-to-air%20weapons.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20ultimately%20a%20homegrown%20Chinese%20project%2C%20it%20drew%20inspiration%20from%20abroad%2C%20including%20input%20fr